He was close to his mother, but it was a complicated relationship... She is gone and he did try to have as good of a relationship with his Mom as he could. So that hit piece is just gross. One silver lining is that it does shed some needed light on the fact that men can be victims, too. Just being female doesn't mean we are automatically angels. I'm so sick of this idea that we can't do as much physical damage as a man can. So it's no big deal if we slap, hit, kick, etc. Abuse is abuse and it leaves a scar regardless of the actual level of physical damage. comment:
I'm getting really tired of this cancel culture. Whether it's from woke Hollywood or the masses of mob fandom. 

It's JUST her birthday. That's it. Nothing more, nothing less. This has nothing to do with her and Johnny's fight with each other. 

Do I believe she's guilty? Yes. But what's that got to do with having a birthday?? One may not like her. And that's fine. YOU don't have to wish her a happy birthday. 

But if someone else wishes her a happy birthday and you don't like it, why attack them for wishing her a happy birthday?? That's got nothing to do with you. 

So, what's the deal with attacking Warner Bros for wishing Amber a happy birthday?!! That's not a crime. 

One shouldn't have to feel guilty for wishing another a happy birthday just because the masses don't like her.

Everyone has the right to have at least one special day a year. Whether you like them or not. People need to take a chill pill. The hate is unreal. 

Yes, I think Amber is guilty with Johnny. But I don't hate. Let the courts decide her fate. We need to stop being social judge, jury and executioner. Just let her have her one day. 

I'd be saying the same thing if the roles were reversed and Johnny was the one with the birthday. That's it. Peace. ‚úå -OG
